		    			<article ><div><div class="row" data-mode="readonly" data-snippet="1"><div class="col-md-12"><div class="page-head"><div class="page-title"><h1>Emergency </h1><h2></h2></div><div class="page-details"><ul class="article-category"><li><a href="                /en/search/t/592
            ">
			Emergency
		</a></li><li><a href="                /en/search/t/595
            ">
			COVID-19
		</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,255);"></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><h2 style="font-size:3em;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);font-size:18px;"><b> Information Regarding the COVID-19</b></span></h2><div><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);font-size:18px;"><b>                                                                                       </b> </span></div><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;color:rgb(204,0,51);"><b style="color:rgb(0,0,0);">■Osaka Prefecture Coronavirus Emergency Measures (Outline) </b><br /><b>・</b><a href="http://www.pref.osaka.lg.jp.e.agb.hp.transer.com/iryo/osakakansensho/corona.html" title="" style="font-weight:bold;">About new coronavirus infectious disease </a><b><i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></b></span></span></p><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;color:rgb(204,0,51);"><b>■</b></span></span><a href="https://s3-ap-northeast-1.amazonaws.com/content.osaka-info.jp/octb/emergency/Information_regarding_temporary_closures_and_schedule.pdf" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Information regarding temporary closures and schedule changes in order to minimise the spread of the novel coronavirus  (COVID-19), updated as of July 17th. </a><br /></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><br /></div><b>　■Notice from Immigration Services Agency of Japan<br /></b><p><b></b><span style="font-size:14px;">　Due to the spread of the new coronavirus infection, the target of foreigners who cannot enter Japan has been expanded. It will be as follows from midnight on July 1, 2020.
<br />　1. Foreign nationals holding a Chinese passport issued at Hubei or Zhejiang of the People's Republic of China</span><span style="font-size:14px;"><br />　2. Foreigners who have stayed in the areas in Table within 14 days prior their arrival in Japan<br />　<b><u>Table</u></b>　<br />　Iceland, Ireland, Azerbaijan, Afghanistan, United Arab Emirates, Algeria, Argentina, Albania, Armenia, Antigua/Barbuda, Andorra, Israel, Italy, Iraq, Iran, India, Indonesia, Ukraine, Uruguay, United Kingdom, Ecuador, Egypt, Estonia, Eswatini, El Salvador, Australia, Austria, Oman, Netherlands, Guyana, Kazakhstan, Qatar, Canada, Ghana, Cape Verde, Gabon, Cameroon, South Korea, North Macedonia, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Cyprus, Cuba, Greece, Kyrgyzstan, Guatemala, Kuwait, Granada, Croatia, Costa Rica, Kosovo, Columbia, Democratic Republic of Congo, Cote d'Ivoire, Saudi Arabia, Sao Tome and Principe, San Marino, Djibouti, Jamaica, Georgia, Singapore, Switzerland, Sweden, Spain, Slovakia, Slovenia, Equatorial Guinea, Senegal, Serbia, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Tajikistan, Thailand, Taiwan, Czech Republic, China, Chile, Central Africa, Denmark, Germany, Commonwealth of Dominica, Dominican Republic, Turkey, Nicaragua, New Zealand, Norway, Haiti, Pakistan, Vatican, Panama, Bahamas, Hungary, Bahrain, Barbados, Bangladesh, Philippines, Finland, Brazil, France, Bulgaria, Brunei, USA, Vietnam, Belarus, Belgium, Peru, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Poland, Bolivia, Portugal, Honduras, Malta, Malaysia, South Africa, Mexico, Monaco, Mauritania, Maldives, Moldova, Morocco, Montenegro, Mauritius, Latvia, Lithuania, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg, Romania, Lebanon, Russia　<br /></span></p></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><br /></div><b>　■Visa Restrictions<br /></b><p><b></b><span style="font-size:14px;">　Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan　<a href="https://www.mofa.go.jp/index.html" title="">（Official website <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> ）</a><br />　Ministry of Justice <a href="http://www.moj.go.jp/EN/nyuukokukanri/kouhou/m_nyuukokukanri01_00003.html" title=""> （Official website <span class="icon ion-android-open"></span>）</a></span><span style="font-size:14px;"><br />　Kansai International Airoport （<a href="https://www.kansai-airport.or.jp/en/notices/3040" title="">Official website  </a><i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> )<br />　■</span><b><a href="https://www.mofa.go.jp/region/index.html" title=""><span style="font-size:14px;">Embassies and Consulate Generals （Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan website)</span></a><i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></b></p></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;">We at the Osaka Convention and Tourism Bureau are working closely alongside  as well as both the Osaka City and Osaka Prefectural governments in order to provide up-to-date information to all visitors. <br />We are currently operating the following consultation and advice services.</span></span><br /><b style="font-size:1.05em;"></b></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><h2 style="font-size:3em;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);font-size:18px;"><b></b></span></h2><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-weight:bold;color:rgb(0,0,0);">■Consultation Services for Residets in Osaka</span><a href="https://www.ofix.or.jp/life/index_e.html" title=""><br /><span style="font-size:14px;"><b>  ・</b></span></a><a href="https://www.ofix.or.jp/english/index.html" title=""><b><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);">Osaka Foundation of International Exchange (OFIX)  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></span></b></a></span><br /><span style="font-size:14px;">   Tel : 06-6941-2297<br />   Open: Mon. &amp; Fri 9:00 -20:00 (except national holidays), Tues., Wed. &amp; Thurs. 9:00-  17:30 (except national holidays)
2nd &amp; 4th Sun. of each month 13:00-17:00<br />Languages:English, Chinese, Korean, Portuguese, Spanish, Vietnamese, Filipino, Thai, Indonesian, Nepali, Japanese</span></span></span></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><h2 style="font-size:3em;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);font-size:18px;"><b></b></span></h2><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;">  ・<a href="https://www.ih-osaka.or.jp/english/information_center/" title=""><b style="color:rgb(0,0,0);">Osaka International House of Osaka </b> <b style="color:rgb(0,0,0);">  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></b></a></span><br /><span style="font-size:14px;">   Tel : 06-6773-6533<br />  Open: Mon. &amp; Fri 9:00 -20:00 (except national holidays), Tues., Wed. &amp; Thurs. 9:00-17:30 (except national holidays)
2nd &amp; 4th Sun. of each month 13:00-17:00<br />  Languages:English, Chinese, Korean, Portuguese, Spanish, Vietnamese, Filipino, Thai, Indonesian, Nepali, Japanese</span></span><span style="text-align:center;font-size:14px;">　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　</span></p><p></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><div class="col-md-12 center"><h2 style="font-size:3em;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);font-size:18px;"><b></b></span></h2><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><b style="font-size:14px;">■Consultation Services for Visitors to Osaka from Abroad.</b><br /><span style="font-size:14px;"><b>【Telephone Consultation Services and Inquiry Counters】</b></span><br /><span style="font-size:14px;">  ・ We at the Osaka Convention and Tourism Bureau have opened the following telephone consultation services and inquiry counters.</span><br /><span style="font-size:14px;"><a href="http://ofw-oer.com/call/en/" title="">Osaka Call Center   <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a><br />Tourist Information Centres   </span></span><span style="font-size:14px;">(<a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-shin-osaka" title="">Shin-Osaka <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a> , <a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-osaka" title="">Osaka <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a>,<a href="https://osaka-info.jp/en/page/tourist-information-namba" title=""> Namba <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a>).</span><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;"><br /></span></span></p><p></p><p style="text-align:left;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;">・The Japan National Tourism Association (JNTO) operates a 24-hour Japan Visitor Hotline. This multilingual hotline can be used for accident and emergency situations as well as for general tourist information. If you require emergency support or advice, please contact the following number.   <a href="https://www.japan.travel/en/plan/hotline/" title="">Japan　Visitor Hotline <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a>     Tel  050-3816-2787</span></span></p><p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,153);"><span style="font-size:14px;"><b>【Online Information Regarding Medical Facilities】</b><br />　For additional information regarding medical facilities with multilingual support:<br />・Osaka Prefectural Government Homepage “Osaka Medical Net for Foreigners”:　<a href="https://www.mfis.pref.osaka.jp/omfo/" title="">https://www.mfis.pref.osaka.jp/omfo/ <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></a><br /><b>・<a href="https://www.osakasafetravels.com/en/" title="">Osaka Safe Travels </a><i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></b>　To ensure the safety of overseas travelers,
provides disaster-related information such as emergency shelters and transportation.
Must-visit website while traveling in Osaka. <br />・The Japan National Tourism Association Homepage 　<a href="https://www.jnto.go.jp/emergency/eng/mi_guide.html" title="">https://www.jnto.go.jp/emergency/eng/mi_guide.html </a><i class="icon ion-android-open"></i></span></span></p><p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="text-align:center;font-size:18px;">We wish a safe and enjoyable stay to all of those visiting Osaka at this present time.</span></p>　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　　<br /><p></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="7"><div class="col-md-12"><hr /></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="7"><div class="col-md-12"><hr /></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4"><br /><div class="row" data-snippet="4"><div class="col-md-12"><p><span style="color:inherit;font-size:1.73em;letter-spacing:0px;">Telephone numbers in case of emergency</span><br />This is a list of contact information which you need to know in case of emergency such as accidents, natural disasters or injuries, etc. for notification and information gathering.It is effective that you confirm the contact information in advance so as to stay calm and act properly in case of emergency.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="row" data-snippet="4"><div class="col-md-12"><p><b>Crime/ Accident</b><br />Please call the emergency number of the police " 110".<br /><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/1/1/3954.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">How to call Dial 110</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i>  (Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）<br />【Reference】<br /><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/2/index.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">The Police Box ("Koban") at Minami and Kita area</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）<br /><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/2/3958.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Information about police stations in Osaka city</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）<br /><a href="https://www.police.pref.osaka.lg.jp/foreign_languag_selection/english/3/2/3957.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Information about police stations outside Osaka city</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Osaka Prefectural Police Department）<br /></p><p><b>Fire / Ambulance</b><br />Please call the emergency number of the fire department " 119".<br /><a href="http://www.city.osaka.lg.jp/contents/wdu020/shobo/english/e03/if_02.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">How to call Dial 119</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Osaka Municipal Fire Department）<br /></p></div></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4"><div class="col-md-12"><h3>Disasters</h3><p><a href="http://www.jnto.go.jp/safety-tips/pc/index.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Safety tips for travelers</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i>  (Website of the Japan Tourism Agency)<br />The purpose of this website is to provide information to ensure safe travel for foreign tourists visiting Japan.<br /><a href="http://www.jnto.go.jp/eng/arrange/essential/emergency/safety_tips.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Application"Safety tips"</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i>  (Website of JNTO)<br />"Safety tips" is a push-enabled app for Earthquake Early Warning and Tsunami Warning within Japan<br /><a href="http://www.osaka-bousai.net.e.add.hp.transer.com/pref/index.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Osaka disaster prevention net</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of Osaka Prefecture）<br /><a href="http://www.mlit.go.jp/river/bousai/olympic/en/index.html" title="" target="_blank" style="background-color:rgb(255,255,255);font-size:16px;" rel="noreferrer noopener">Disaster Prevention Portal</a><span style="font-size:14px;">  </span><i class="icon ion-android-open" style="font-size:14px;"></i><span style="font-size:14px;">  (Website of the Ministry of Land, Infrastructure, Transport and Tourism)<br /></span><span style="font-size:14px;">This portal site provides information related to disasters that may occur in Tokyo as well as useful disaster prevention information. This is a precautionary measure taken in case the Tokyo metropolitan area is directly affected by harmful seismic activity. In particular, it has been set up in preparation for the 2020 Olympic and Paralympic games in Tokyo. </span></p><p></p><div class="edit"><br /></div><p></p></div></div><div class="row" data-snippet="4"><div class="col-md-12"><h3>Others</h3><p><a href="http://www.mofa.go.jp/about/emb_cons/protocol/index.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Embassies and Consulates in Japan</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i>  (Website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan）<br /><a href="http://www.ofix.or.jp/english/index.html" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Osaka Information Service for Foreign Residents</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i>  (Website of the Osaka Foundation of International Exchange(OFIX))<br /><a href="http://www.ofw-oer.com/en/" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Osaka Free WiFi</a>  <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Osaka Convention &amp; Tourism Bureau）<br /><a href="https://www.japan.travel/en/plan/#search" title="" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Helping You Plan</a>    <i class="icon ion-android-open"></i> （Website of the Japan National Tourism Organization(JNTO)）</p><p><br /></p></div></div><div><div class="row" data-snippet="8"><div class="col-md-12"><br /><br /></div></div></div></article>
	
